description: The Counseling exam skills provide simulations that are in the format as the licensing NCMHCE exam. It provides practice and instruction of the narrative process necessary to pass the NCMHCE to be licensed as a LPC, LCPC, LPCC, LMHC, LPCMH, LCMHC, LPC-MH at the state level. Feedback helps analyze the case simulations and build critical skills for passing the counseling exam including diagnostic, treatment, continuum of care and professional practice skills.
name: Counseling Exam
shortDescription: The Counseling exam skill provides review material study for the national clinical mental health exam (the NCMHCE) to become a licensed counselor.
